      "updated_at": "2016-05-05T09:44:22Z",
      "body": "weex-loader v0.1.4 published!  You can use like this to solve the problem:\n\n**demo.we**\n\n```\n<template>\n   <container class=\"a b\"></container>\n</template>\n\n<style>\na {\n  color: red\n}\n</style>\n\n<script>\nmodule.exports = {\n   data: {}\n}\n\nmodule.exports.style = require('./ex.css')\n</script>\n```\n\n**ex.css**\n\n```\nb {\n  font-size: 32;\n}\n```\n"
